-- 
Greek Government Spokesman Confirms Troika Call at 7 P.M. Today

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-09-19T13:28:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/greek-government-spokesman-confirms-troika-call-at-7-p-m-today.html
Greek government spokesman Ilias
Mosialos confirmed news reports that Finance Minister Evangelos
Venizelos will hold a conference call with the heads of the
European Union and International Monetary Fund mission to  Athens 
at 7 p.m. local time today.  The call was moved from 3 p.m. because of the time
difference with the U.S., Mosialos told a Greek radio station
today, according to an emailed transcript of his statements.
“Today it’s on the techical details, then there will need to be
consultations with individual ministers, and then we will see
when the ministerial meeting will be held,” he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  